Class AbstractObjectIterator<K>

java.lang.Object
it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects.AbstractObjectIterator<K>
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
AbstractObjectBidirectionalIterator, ObjectBigListIterators.AbstractIndexBasedBigIterator, ObjectIterators.AbstractIndexBasedIterator
public abstract class AbstractObjectIterator<K> extends Object implements ObjectIterator<K>
An abstract class facilitating the creation of type-specific iterators.
API Notes:
Up to version 8.5.0, this class was deprecated as abstract methods were turned into default methods of the type-specific interface. Now the class hosts finalized versions of default delegating methods such as Iterator.forEachRemaining(java.util.function.Consumer<? super E>).
